# Walkthrough: Simplified Approval Buttons

I have updated the approval buttons on the **Leave Requests** page to provide a cleaner and more professional user interface.

## Changes Made

### 1. Label Standardization
I removed the role suffixes (e.g., `(OM)`, `(HOD)`, `(GM)`, `(CEO)`) from the approval buttons. Since these buttons only appear for the relevant logged-in user, the context is already implied, and removing the text makes the interface less cluttered.

#### [Requests.tsx](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/src/pages/Requests.tsx)
- Updated both the **Desktop Table View** and the **Mobile Card View**.
- Changed "Approve (OM)", "Approve (HOD)", "Approve (GM)", and "Approve (CEO)" to simply **"Approve"**.

## Verification Results

### Automated Tests
I verified that the search for the old strings returns no results in the file:

```bash
grep -E "Approve \((HOD|OM|GM|CEO)\)" src/pages/Requests.tsx
```

> [!NOTE]
> All labels now consistently use the simplified "Approve" text across all approval levels.

